♪ Got a ♪

01:50.891 --> 01:53.563
Man: [ Laughs ] Yeah!

01:54.000 --> 01:55.171
Dealer: Come on.

01:55.219 --> 01:57.938
Craig: All right, here we go.
Go big or go home.

01:57.986 --> 02:00.266
Stick with me, guys,
you wanna make that money.

02:00.405 --> 02:01.704
Winner!

02:01.780 --> 02:03.081
[ Cheering ]

02:03.208 --> 02:05.821
[ Speaks indistinctly ] Go.

02:05.889 --> 02:07.547
♪♪

02:07.595 --> 02:09.297
He wins again!

02:09.485 --> 02:11.258
[ Laughs ]

02:11.790 --> 02:13.235
- Bring it! Bring it here.
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

02:13.283 --> 02:14.821
[ Lowered voice ]
You got any blow?

02:15.149 --> 02:16.785
[ Chips clink ]

02:16.936 --> 02:19.038
♪ Who's the man? ♪
♪ You the man ♪

02:19.102 --> 02:20.758
♪ Who's the man? ♪
♪ You the man ♪

02:20.806 --> 02:22.602
♪ I been dreaming about
living it large ♪

02:22.650 --> 02:24.984
♪ Here I am now, I'm in charge ♪
- ♪ Yeah ♪

02:25.064 --> 02:27.469
♪ Who's the man? ♪
♪ You the man ♪

02:27.536 --> 02:29.204
♪ Who's the man?
♪ You the man

02:29.252 --> 02:30.774
♪ Do it now with
the era of the kings ♪

02:30.822 --> 02:32.860
♪ Bow down and kiss the ring

02:32.908 --> 02:36.618
♪♪

02:36.666 --> 02:40.336
♪♪

02:42.247 --> 02:47.040
♪♪ Glass Animals' "Gooey"
playing...

02:47.155 --> 02:52.282
♪ Spinning 'round my head
and I stare ♪

02:52.353 --> 02:57.458
♪ While my naked fool ♪

02:57.593 --> 03:02.344
♪ Fresh out
of an icky, gooey womb ♪

03:02.494 --> 03:07.844
♪ A woozy youth ♪

03:07.992 --> 03:13.219
♪ Dopes up
on her silky smooth perfume ♪

03:13.369 --> 03:18.352
♪ Ride my little Pooh bear,
wanna take a chance ♪

03:18.501 --> 03:23.454
♪ Wanna sip this smooth air,
kick it in the sand ♪

03:23.573 --> 03:28.930
♪ I'd say I told you so
but you just gonna cry ♪

03:29.064 --> 03:34.204
♪ You just wanna know
those peanut butter vibes ♪

03:34.340 --> 03:39.407
♪ My, my, simple sir,
this ain't gonna work ♪

03:39.550 --> 03:45.118
♪ I just wanna go where
I can get some space ♪

03:45.510 --> 03:49.844
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:50.071 --> 03:52.782
Man: Dude, can I have two shots?
Two shots.

03:52.918 --> 03:56.750
♪♪

03:57.267 --> 03:59.774
Hey, can you pour this guy
some shots?

04:03.262 --> 04:05.196
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:05.244 --> 04:06.844
You're becoming a regular here,
man.

04:06.892 --> 04:09.899
[ Chuckles ]
I brought you something.

04:10.336 --> 04:13.500
Is there somewhere quieter?

04:14.461 --> 04:16.415
Found it while I was packing.

04:16.793 --> 04:19.750
Thought you might want
to hang it somewhere.

04:20.438 --> 04:22.329
Packing?

04:22.863 --> 04:26.290
Uh, I'm taking one last shot
at the Q.S.

04:26.553 --> 04:28.000
Leaving Tuesday.

04:28.142 --> 04:29.977
What about school?

04:30.157 --> 04:31.454
[ Chuckles ]

04:31.867 --> 04:35.274
I'll make it up next semester.

04:36.371 --> 04:39.579
I always got so nervous
when I was competing.

04:40.139 --> 04:42.776
You'd be smoking a joint,
and they'd call your name,

04:42.844 --> 04:46.321
and you'd be like,
"All right. Here, hold this."

04:47.813 --> 04:49.852
Yeah, well, the weed helped.

04:50.112 --> 04:52.399
No, I think you were
just that good.

04:52.563 --> 04:54.461
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:55.128 --> 04:57.391
That's the last time I won.

04:57.606 --> 04:58.774
Mm-hmm.

04:58.973 --> 05:01.188
Lately you seem like that again.

05:01.369 --> 05:02.750
Like what?

05:02.910 --> 05:05.321
Like that kid I grew up with.

05:05.870 --> 05:09.579
♪♪

05:09.626 --> 05:13.297
♪♪

05:13.404 --> 05:17.157
♪♪

05:17.204 --> 05:21.024
♪♪

05:21.094 --> 05:24.368
♪♪

05:24.533 --> 05:27.368
[ Inhales deeply,
exhales slowly ]

05:27.962 --> 05:30.196
I'll see you when I get back.

05:30.278 --> 05:34.118
♪♪

05:36.512 --> 05:40.352
♪♪

05:44.265 --> 05:47.954
♪♪

05:55.024 --> 05:58.930
♪♪

06:03.314 --> 06:05.516
[ Exhales deeply ]

06:07.000 --> 06:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:19.320 --> 06:21.233
[ Sighs ]

06:21.385 --> 06:25.178
♪♪

06:33.339 --> 06:35.686
[ Door opens ]

06:38.335 --> 06:39.538
Come to bed.

06:39.673 --> 06:42.413
Yeah, in a minute.

06:42.692 --> 06:44.897
- [ Exhales deeply ] Hey.
- [ Whispers ] Hey.

06:46.450 --> 06:48.017
[ Inhales deeply ]

06:48.216 --> 06:50.296
When you are gonna tell
the others?

06:50.563 --> 06:52.507
When it's done.

06:52.707 --> 06:54.409
You think Smurf knows?

06:54.632 --> 06:57.921
[ Chuckles ]
By now she knows, yeah.

06:58.709 --> 07:01.233
She's gonna try to get
to your brothers first.

07:01.453 --> 07:03.264
You sure they'll choose you?

07:03.788 --> 07:05.163
Come on.

07:05.519 --> 07:08.054
What about the kid?
You trust him?

07:08.102 --> 07:11.257
No, I don't trust him,
but I know how to handle him.

07:12.868 --> 07:15.257
Es la madre de ellos.

07:15.997 --> 07:17.633
Now you sound like Cath.

07:17.704 --> 07:18.936
[ Glasses thud ]

07:19.084 --> 07:20.318
[ Cork pops ]

07:20.375 --> 07:21.741
Just be smart. [ Sighs ]

07:21.789 --> 07:22.797
With all that money,

07:22.845 --> 07:24.757
you'd never have to work
in your life again.

07:24.981 --> 07:26.295
Deran could take care of Craig,

07:26.351 --> 07:28.675
but Pope's dead in a year
without me, so...

07:28.723 --> 07:30.358
[ Bottle thuds ]

07:31.389 --> 07:33.772
You'd do anything for Marco.

07:34.467 --> 07:36.069
Not anything.

07:36.285 --> 07:39.311
♪♪

07:39.359 --> 07:40.702
[ Glass thuds ]

07:40.846 --> 07:43.132
Don't ever say
I sound like Catherine again.

07:43.433 --> 07:44.558
Okay, I won't.

07:44.606 --> 07:46.085
It takes me three minutes
to pack.

07:46.133 --> 07:48.366
Oh,
you're threatening me now?

07:49.218 --> 07:50.678
I'm just going to bed.

07:50.787 --> 07:52.100
I have to work early tomorrow.

07:52.154 --> 07:53.922
Oh, yeah, I forgot.

07:53.979 --> 07:56.178
You're really important.

07:56.936 --> 07:59.038
Sí, I am.

07:59.089 --> 08:00.850
I know you are.

08:01.099 --> 08:05.038
♪♪

08:08.062 --> 08:10.928
[ Water running ]

08:11.199 --> 08:12.901
[ Turns faucet off ]

08:30.386 --> 08:32.198
Is this for me?

08:32.580 --> 08:34.749
[ Voice breaking ]
Yeah. I got it for you.

08:34.836 --> 08:36.878
What's the matter?

08:37.847 --> 08:41.347
Chris just told me that
his curtains are "opaque."

08:41.464 --> 08:43.292
[ Chuckles ]

08:44.083 --> 08:45.229
What?

08:45.287 --> 08:47.878
Opaque? [ Chuckles, sniffles ]

08:49.050 --> 08:51.058
It's the worst part...

08:51.903 --> 08:54.738
you know, not hearing his voice
every day.

08:55.060 --> 08:56.558
Every time I talk to him,

08:56.606 --> 08:59.777
it's like he's...
It's like he's a new kid.

09:00.631 --> 09:02.065
You'll get him back.

09:02.216 --> 09:05.157
You know,
he likes his school.

09:05.796 --> 09:10.314
He has friends. He's...
he's happy there.

09:10.959 --> 09:13.353
Amy...

09:16.164 --> 09:18.967
you're his mom.

09:26.603 --> 09:28.048
[ Sniffles ]

09:34.653 --> 09:39.282
Hey, do you wanna
come with me on Saturday?

09:39.996 --> 09:42.931
Chris has a baseball game.

09:43.587 --> 09:45.407
I want you to meet him.

09:45.617 --> 09:47.052
What about your brother?

09:47.202 --> 09:51.025
♪♪

09:51.604 --> 09:54.072
He'll understand
that it's important.

09:59.249 --> 10:00.903
Okay.

10:02.303 --> 10:04.044
Great.

10:06.099 --> 10:08.278
Nicky: Craig texted me again.

10:08.712 --> 10:11.895
- Listen to this.
- [ Clears throat ]

10:12.247 --> 10:13.653
"You're a cool girl,

10:13.704 --> 10:15.327
and I've really enjoyed
our time together."

10:15.375 --> 10:17.855
- [ Chuckles ]
- "Our time together"? [ Laughs ]

10:18.621 --> 10:21.066
"But I think we are better
as friends."

10:21.429 --> 10:24.027
Okay, we are not friends.
We have never been friends.

10:24.232 --> 10:25.824
It's like talking to a steak.

10:25.872 --> 10:27.293
[ Man calling sports game
on TV ]

10:27.349 --> 10:28.941
- [ Chuckles ]
- Are you okay?

10:29.114 --> 10:30.691
Yeah.

10:31.176 --> 10:33.910
He gives me my share from
the boat, I don't give a shit.

10:34.093 --> 10:36.691
[ Cellphone chimes ]
I...

10:37.606 --> 10:39.508
He says, um,

10:39.721 --> 10:41.988
"We can still hook up
if you want."

10:42.299 --> 10:43.582
He's high.

10:43.723 --> 10:46.151
He forgot he already
broke up with me 11 times...

10:46.199 --> 10:47.651
Three times yesterday.

10:47.871 --> 10:49.640
Also, dude, text?

10:49.735 --> 10:52.772
Come on. You're, like, 40.
Grow up.

10:52.930 --> 10:54.113
- He's not 40.
- [ Laughs ]

10:54.161 --> 10:55.433
[ Laughs ]

10:56.025 --> 10:58.627
[ Beer sloshes ]

11:00.586 --> 11:01.588
Oh.

11:01.636 --> 11:02.900
Do you want me to go
get you another one?

11:02.948 --> 11:05.143
No. No, it's fine.
You can have it.

11:05.324 --> 11:06.807
Thanks.

11:07.407 --> 11:11.760
[ TV continues indistinctly ]

11:12.280 --> 11:13.971
Do you think
I'll have to move?

11:14.115 --> 11:17.166
[ Men speaking indistinctly
on TV ]

11:17.485 --> 11:18.994
No.

11:19.287 --> 11:21.096
I'll talk to Smurf.

11:21.975 --> 11:23.869
Thanks.

11:25.088 --> 11:26.924
[ Sighs ]

11:34.528 --> 11:35.822
Smurf?

11:36.370 --> 11:38.088
[ Touchscreen clicking ]

11:40.135 --> 11:42.065
[ Shovel thudding ]

11:45.112 --> 11:46.572
Smurf?

11:46.750 --> 11:47.947
What are you doing?

11:48.582 --> 11:51.423
I keep an emergency fund
out here.

11:51.708 --> 11:54.619
Let me do it. I'll do it.

11:56.064 --> 11:57.576
[ Shovel thudding ]

11:57.624 --> 12:00.460
You always need
to have cash on hand.

12:00.861 --> 12:04.173
Keeps you mobile, adaptable.

12:04.283 --> 12:05.344
[ Dirt sifts ]

12:05.463 --> 12:08.869
Without cash, you're just...
you're vulnerable.

12:09.152 --> 12:10.787
What about your cut
from the yacht heist?

12:10.835 --> 12:13.486
No, no. Way too soon
to fence that.

12:13.673 --> 12:15.540
We have to wait.

12:15.690 --> 12:18.126
[ Shovel dragging on ground ]

12:18.345 --> 12:20.376
[ Metal clanking ]
There. Okay.

12:21.682 --> 12:23.392
Pull it out.

12:32.991 --> 12:36.330
Baz ripped off
my storage unit.

12:38.915 --> 12:40.204
How do you know?

12:40.276 --> 12:44.361
Everything I do, I do for this
family. You know that, right?

12:44.858 --> 12:46.525
Yeah.

12:47.715 --> 12:49.595
What are you gonna do
to him?

12:53.682 --> 12:57.697
Families are complicated.
Right?

12:57.869 --> 13:00.962
Here. You lay off
the credit card for a while

13:01.255 --> 13:03.197
till I work this out.

13:03.465 --> 13:07.126
♪♪

13:12.333 --> 13:13.634
[ Dirt sifts ]

13:15.403 --> 13:18.259
[ Door creaks open ]

13:27.162 --> 13:30.267
Craig? Wake up.

13:30.315 --> 13:33.535
[ Groans ] You were supposed
to meet me an hour ago.

13:33.651 --> 13:35.634
[ Groans ] How'd you find me?

13:35.844 --> 13:37.384
You gave me the address.

13:37.573 --> 13:39.001
Who are these people?

13:39.192 --> 13:42.001
Hell if I know. You should get
a shot of penicillin.

13:42.049 --> 13:43.064
[ Craig groans ]

13:43.135 --> 13:45.738
Get dressed.
I'll be outside.

13:47.801 --> 13:50.119
[ Door creaks ]

13:53.853 --> 13:55.220
[ Grunts ]

13:57.652 --> 13:59.012
[ Thud ]

13:59.340 --> 14:00.668
[ Door closes ]

14:01.182 --> 14:04.152
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

14:13.656 --> 14:14.858
[ Marco laughs ]

14:14.906 --> 14:16.073
Where are we?

14:16.121 --> 14:18.281
Van Nuys.

14:19.223 --> 14:21.292
[ Keys jangle ] I'll call
you in a couple hours,

14:21.340 --> 14:23.953
give you the address
so you can drop off the car.

14:25.783 --> 14:27.084
Wait. What?

14:27.141 --> 14:28.693
We already talked about this.
You owe me.

14:28.741 --> 14:30.434
Yo, I'm not going anywhere
near the border.

14:30.482 --> 14:35.210
No border. Just babysit the car.
Easiest 5K you'll ever make.

14:36.232 --> 14:39.062
Oh, and keep it out the sun.

14:50.446 --> 14:52.181
[ Keys jangle ]

14:59.542 --> 15:02.222
[ Pounding ]

15:02.293 --> 15:03.477
[ Muffled screaming ]

15:03.511 --> 15:07.678
[ Pounding continues ]

15:11.119 --> 15:14.788
♪♪

15:34.734 --> 15:36.359
Is Mommy dead?

15:36.677 --> 15:40.250
♪♪

15:43.315 --> 15:45.750
Is Mommy here?

15:54.120 --> 15:56.346
Hey. Can you drive me
to school?

15:56.394 --> 15:57.814
- [ Inhales deeply ]
- I have a chem final,

15:57.862 --> 15:59.674
and if I don't show up
and bubble in some answers...

15:59.722 --> 16:01.495
[ Grunts ] ...Mr. Erickson
is gonna fail me.

16:01.573 --> 16:03.909
Also, Max has some coke
and he's gonna sell me some.

16:04.010 --> 16:06.659
- [ Sighs ]
- Can you borrow Smurf's car?

16:07.062 --> 16:08.503
Uh, yeah. Sure.

16:08.613 --> 16:10.481
Thanks.

16:14.050 --> 16:15.476
[ Sighs ]

16:15.628 --> 16:18.253
[ Shower running ]

16:18.518 --> 16:20.603
I mean, just 'cause we share
a bathroom

16:20.651 --> 16:22.259
doesn't mean you need
to come into room and...

16:22.307 --> 16:24.182
Yes, it does. That's actually
what it means.

16:24.230 --> 16:26.745
-[Laughs] It means I can come look at you.
- It means it's okay?

16:26.854 --> 16:27.932
- Oh. Hey.
- Hey.

16:27.980 --> 16:29.792
- Hey.  - Hi.
- What are you doing here?

16:29.840 --> 16:31.010
- My kid inside?

16:31.058 --> 16:32.784
- Yeah.
- Good.

16:33.193 --> 16:34.828
- Can I have the keys?
- Yes.

16:35.057 --> 16:36.565
- [ Whispers ] Bye.
- Bye.

16:36.613 --> 16:39.370
Um, you know Smurf knows
it was you, man.

16:39.628 --> 16:41.440
Good.
[ Car door opens ]

16:41.661 --> 16:43.190
I didn't say anything.
[ Car door closes ]

16:43.238 --> 16:44.885
Don't worry, man. I'm not gonna
tell her you helped.

16:45.175 --> 16:47.041
This is for you.

16:49.619 --> 16:51.315
There's a lot more
where that came from.

16:51.471 --> 16:53.131
[ Pats arm ]
Wish me luck.

16:53.179 --> 16:55.041
[ Woman on radio ]
Your skin deserves the rest.

16:55.089 --> 16:56.393
[ Gate opens ]

16:56.441 --> 16:59.611
♪♪ [ Station changes ]
Rock music playing...

16:59.659 --> 17:03.479
♪♪

17:04.223 --> 17:05.800
[ Sighs ]

17:06.888 --> 17:08.346
[ Engine starts ]

17:08.394 --> 17:09.846
Ready?

17:10.362 --> 17:12.214
[ Engine revs ]

17:12.439 --> 17:14.237
Like this?

17:14.634 --> 17:15.971
Lena.

17:16.085 --> 17:17.596
Daddy, look! We're making pie!

17:17.644 --> 17:18.854
Yeah, kiddo, come on.

17:18.902 --> 17:20.573
Go get your clothes on.
We're late here.

17:20.743 --> 17:22.330
Okay, go.

17:26.311 --> 17:28.181
You should've told me
you were coming, Baz.

17:28.214 --> 17:29.596
I would've made you breakfast.

17:29.668 --> 17:33.385
Well, I've been avoiding you.

17:33.787 --> 17:35.689
[ Coffee pouring ]
$1.4 million in cash,

17:35.722 --> 17:38.784
10 times that when I sell the rest.
[ Coffee pot clatters ]

17:39.135 --> 17:40.979
Planning on keeping it
for yourself?

17:41.055 --> 17:42.591
No, I'm gonna split it evenly,

17:42.702 --> 17:44.401
like you should have been
doing for years.

17:44.635 --> 17:46.440
Really? How do you know
I wasn't?

17:46.534 --> 17:50.089
Oh, right. It's all for us.
Is that right?

17:50.554 --> 17:52.237
Is that why you kept
the watches?

17:52.475 --> 17:55.778
If you knew that we were
sitting on those watches,

17:55.976 --> 17:57.706
you would lose it.

17:57.969 --> 18:00.137
A few years from now,
I sell those watches...

18:00.280 --> 18:01.745
[ Snaps fingers ]
like that.

18:01.793 --> 18:02.932
And pocket the cash?

18:02.992 --> 18:05.839
No, I spread it among my family,
like always.

18:06.119 --> 18:07.409
It's called management.

18:07.519 --> 18:10.260
Or you're keeping evidence
on us.

18:10.936 --> 18:12.571
You're gonna sign
the Condon building

18:12.620 --> 18:14.922
and the Deacon units
over to me.

18:15.018 --> 18:16.784
I'll use them to launder
our money.

18:16.920 --> 18:18.755
You don't come near the jobs.

18:18.880 --> 18:20.518
You don't touch the cash.

18:20.652 --> 18:23.588
What do you think you have left
to threaten me with?

18:23.904 --> 18:25.925
You get to keep your family.

18:26.157 --> 18:28.694
You give me the buildings,
I won't tell your sons that

18:28.742 --> 18:31.104
you've been stealing from them
and keeping evidence on them.

18:31.192 --> 18:32.613
Call me when you have
the paperwork ready.

18:32.646 --> 18:34.745
I'll give you a couple days.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.471
[ Door opens, closes ]

18:42.615 --> 18:46.253
♪♪

18:50.168 --> 18:52.837
[ Car door opens, closes ]

18:53.091 --> 18:55.428
[ Engine starts ]

18:58.092 --> 19:01.128
♪♪

19:03.644 --> 19:06.880
[ Engine starts ]

19:06.913 --> 19:10.205
♪♪

19:15.920 --> 19:17.021
[ Bottle clinks ]

19:17.157 --> 19:18.353
[ Loud bang ]

19:18.539 --> 19:19.548
Craig: Yo!

19:19.596 --> 19:21.095
[ Door slams ]
I need help, man!

19:21.143 --> 19:22.345
- Who is that?
- [ Muffled shouting ]

19:22.393 --> 19:24.313
- I don't know!
- Who is that, Craig?

19:24.361 --> 19:26.127
I don't know, man!
You gonna help me or what?!

19:26.175 --> 19:27.810
[ Muffled shouting continues ]

19:27.858 --> 19:29.822
Yeah, put him
in the office, man.

19:29.939 --> 19:32.463
♪♪

19:32.511 --> 19:34.666
Christ. Stay still!

19:35.149 --> 19:37.387
You hear me? Stay still,
goddamn it!

19:37.697 --> 19:41.384
[ Grunts ] Quit it!
Quit it! Quit it.

19:43.269 --> 19:45.772
[ Chain rattles ]

19:45.947 --> 19:48.095
[ Muffled whimpering ]

19:48.143 --> 19:49.544
[ Locks door ]

19:49.592 --> 19:51.806
Oh, my God, man.
I wake up, like, hungover.

19:52.025 --> 19:54.931
Marco's there, and then
he gives me the key to this car.

19:55.095 --> 19:58.236
He drives off, and this kid's
in the trunk.

19:58.638 --> 20:01.017
And now Marco's not
picking up the phone.

20:01.570 --> 20:03.947
[ Muffled shouting ]

20:03.995 --> 20:05.650
Stay still! You hear me?!

20:05.698 --> 20:06.830
- Craig. Goddamn it,
- Stay.

20:06.878 --> 20:08.705
put him in the chair now, man.

20:08.835 --> 20:10.345
- [ Grunting ]
- Sit down.

20:10.432 --> 20:13.892
You gonna finally shut up?
You gonna shut up?

20:15.381 --> 20:17.025
[ Drawer closes ]

20:17.397 --> 20:18.486
Zip tie.

20:19.104 --> 20:21.139
- Shut up.
- [ Muffled speech ]

20:21.187 --> 20:24.556
- [ Speaking muffled Spanish ]
- Oh, yeah? Yeah, bro?

20:24.716 --> 20:27.322
Shut up. Shut up.

20:28.509 --> 20:29.659
[ Grunts ]

20:29.707 --> 20:30.869
[ Groans ]

20:30.917 --> 20:32.252
[ Zip ties tighten ]

20:35.599 --> 20:38.302
All right. All right, chill.
Shut up. Shut up.

20:38.398 --> 20:39.494
I'm taking this off.

20:39.571 --> 20:42.010
- Hey! I'm taking this off, okay?
- Shut up.

20:42.108 --> 20:43.767
[ Tape rips ]

20:44.969 --> 20:46.971
¿Tienes alguna idea
quien es mi padre?

20:47.113 --> 20:48.517
I don't speak Spanish.

20:48.720 --> 20:50.564
Do you have any idea
who my father is?

20:50.652 --> 20:53.021
No, I don't.
I have no idea who you are.

20:53.205 --> 20:54.892
You're making a big mistake.

20:55.140 --> 20:56.994
No shit. Call Marco right now.

20:57.165 --> 20:59.844
- He's not picking up his phone.
- I don't care, Craig. Call him.

20:59.892 --> 21:01.353
Tell him he's not here
in 15 minutes,

21:01.424 --> 21:02.424
we're dumping this kid
on the street.

21:02.472 --> 21:03.892
Estás muerto, cabrón.

21:04.086 --> 21:05.494
English, please.

21:05.542 --> 21:06.940
You're dead.

21:10.758 --> 21:14.385
♪♪

21:15.120 --> 21:17.096
Victor Reyes.

21:18.681 --> 21:19.895
Is that your name?

21:19.991 --> 21:22.330
No, that's the name of the guy
they'll send

21:22.392 --> 21:23.775
to cut your dicks off.

21:24.190 --> 21:26.249
Then he'll make you eat them.

21:26.619 --> 21:28.697
Whoa, dude.

21:30.283 --> 21:32.510
Look, I was coming home
from school once

21:32.588 --> 21:34.272
when I was, like, 8.

21:34.535 --> 21:36.994
Some guy put me
in the back of a van.

21:37.283 --> 21:41.146
24 hours later, I was
back at home drinking a Yoo-hoo,

21:41.416 --> 21:44.482
and the guys that snatched me
were headless,

21:44.822 --> 21:47.150
hanging from a bridge.

21:49.791 --> 21:51.478
It's up to you.

21:52.572 --> 21:54.002
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

21:54.318 --> 21:56.064
- Okay.
- Yo, Marco.

21:56.427 --> 21:58.215
[ Buzzing continues ]
Give me it.

21:58.385 --> 21:59.931
- Keep an eye on him.
- Yeah.

21:59.965 --> 22:01.260
Marco, where the hell are you?

22:01.308 --> 22:02.807
We've been trying
to reach you for an hour.

22:02.855 --> 22:03.744
Hey, don't me calling me,

22:03.792 --> 22:05.424
leaving me
threatening voicemails, bro.

22:05.636 --> 22:07.900
- Who is this kid?
- I talked to Craig.

22:08.002 --> 22:09.517
- He was cool with it. Okay,
- you've got

22:09.565 --> 22:10.789
30 minutes to come get this kid,

22:10.837 --> 22:11.860
or we're letting him go.

22:11.908 --> 22:13.002
I did you a favor.

22:13.050 --> 22:14.275
Next time you need
a translator,

22:14.323 --> 22:15.353
try Rosetta Stone.

22:15.401 --> 22:17.751
Why is this kid talking about
cutting our dicks off, Marco?

22:17.799 --> 22:19.454
His dad's
some low-level scumbag

22:19.502 --> 22:21.377
who stole some money from
some people he shouldn't have.

22:21.431 --> 22:22.478
He'll pay.

22:22.526 --> 22:24.061
I agreed to do a favor for you.

22:24.230 --> 22:25.597
I thought we were talking
about a pickup,

22:25.645 --> 22:27.400
maybe a border run,
not a kidnapping.

22:27.685 --> 22:30.783
Just hold him for a few hours.
I'll text you an address.

22:30.892 --> 22:32.568
Just drop him off. It's simple.

22:32.602 --> 22:33.903
[ Beep, call disconnects ]

22:33.936 --> 22:35.671
[ Touchscreen clicks ]

22:37.807 --> 22:40.127
[ Sighs ]

22:40.411 --> 22:44.299
♪♪

22:55.451 --> 22:56.787
[ Keys jangle ]

22:57.905 --> 22:59.178
[ Door closes ]

22:59.226 --> 23:01.395
[ Keys jangle ]
Child: <i>I'll see you later!</i>

23:02.225 --> 23:03.798
Okay, come on.

23:03.897 --> 23:07.834
Can I go with you when
you go away? I'll be quiet.

23:08.295 --> 23:09.683
What are you talking about?

23:09.936 --> 23:12.273
I heard you talking to Lucy.

23:14.308 --> 23:16.146
I'm not going anywhere.

23:16.194 --> 23:18.060
And if I ever did,
you would come with me.

23:18.108 --> 23:19.480
You know that, right?

23:19.967 --> 23:22.131
Lena, you know that,
right?

23:22.179 --> 23:23.215
Mm-hmm.

23:23.263 --> 23:24.959
And you don't have to be quiet.
You're a kid.

23:25.084 --> 23:27.014
But you get mad
when I'm loud.

23:27.221 --> 23:30.291
[ Woman shouts indistinctly ]

23:30.858 --> 23:32.866
I don't get mad.

23:33.647 --> 23:35.209
Can Grandma Smurf come?

23:35.272 --> 23:37.701
Lena, I'm not going anywhere.
Come on.

23:38.436 --> 23:41.233
Okay.
Allison's gonna pick you up.

23:41.889 --> 23:43.905
I'll see you later, okay?

23:44.546 --> 23:47.582
[ Rapid footsteps depart ]

23:52.701 --> 23:54.048
J.

23:54.467 --> 23:57.194
Come here. I want you to meet
my friend, Morgan Wilson.

23:57.326 --> 24:00.342
Morgan Wilson, J, my grandson.

24:00.514 --> 24:04.192
Hi. Hi. He looks just
like his mother.

24:04.741 --> 24:07.295
Your grandmother says
you're very bright.

24:07.764 --> 24:09.897
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

24:10.787 --> 24:12.451
It was nice...
Nice to meet you.

24:12.576 --> 24:14.498
I'll be in my room.

24:15.459 --> 24:17.209
J...

24:18.123 --> 24:19.905
Morgan is here to see you.

24:19.953 --> 24:22.022
[ Pats table ]
Sit down.

24:26.414 --> 24:28.182
[ Clears throat ]

24:28.553 --> 24:30.170
Um...

24:31.069 --> 24:33.748
Do you know
what power of attorney is?

24:34.662 --> 24:35.977
No.

24:36.025 --> 24:39.444
For the last 15 years,
Baz has had legal access

24:39.498 --> 24:42.287
to your grandmother's finances,
her properties.

24:42.397 --> 24:45.280
If anything were to happen
to her, well, he'd get...

24:45.342 --> 24:49.084
Everything.
He'd get everything. Okay?

24:49.764 --> 24:50.920
Go on.

24:51.172 --> 24:55.170
Your grandmother says you're
a quick learner, you're loyal,

24:55.366 --> 24:56.888
you're not as emotional
as your uncle.

24:56.936 --> 24:59.811
And I just wanna make sure
that you understand

25:00.029 --> 25:02.850
what a big responsibility
this is, being pow...

25:02.906 --> 25:05.553
What I want to make sure

25:05.756 --> 25:11.125
is that my grandson J is given
my power of attorney now.

25:11.159 --> 25:14.912
♪♪

25:15.756 --> 25:17.057
Are you okay?

25:17.145 --> 25:19.514
Of course I am, baby.

25:20.842 --> 25:22.834
I'll just need your signatures.

25:23.349 --> 25:24.818
[ Pen clicks ]

25:24.959 --> 25:26.600
Where all the stickies are.

25:26.941 --> 25:29.978
♪♪

25:35.855 --> 25:37.824
[ Papers rustling ]

25:38.052 --> 25:41.089
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:47.772 --> 25:49.951
All those man hours.

25:51.311 --> 25:54.235
You got taxpayer dollars,
a SWAT team...

25:54.741 --> 25:56.504
turned up nothing.

25:57.006 --> 25:59.217
But I know you weren't
harassing my family

25:59.272 --> 26:01.795
because we made you
look bad.

26:02.756 --> 26:04.177
Maybe you felt guilty

26:04.225 --> 26:06.623
because Catherine ran off,
left her kid?

26:06.709 --> 26:10.341
You worked her too hard.
She couldn't handle the stress.

26:12.654 --> 26:16.177
Is that why Baz killed her?
He thought she was a C.I.?

26:16.310 --> 26:18.026
Nah, Baz didn't kill anyone.

26:18.256 --> 26:21.646
Yeah? And you didn't burn
her parents to death?

26:23.185 --> 26:25.137
Catherine knew about that,
by the way,

26:25.185 --> 26:26.840
and she still wouldn't talk.

26:26.888 --> 26:28.559
Bullshit.
You were working her.

26:28.607 --> 26:29.709
[ Thud ]

26:29.764 --> 26:31.935
You come at me again,
I will shoot you in the head

26:32.037 --> 26:34.326
and tell the captain
you rushed me.

26:35.724 --> 26:38.193
Catherine wasn't a C.I.

26:39.662 --> 26:41.294
Believe me
or don't believe me,

26:41.342 --> 26:43.021
I don't give a shit.

26:43.232 --> 26:46.951
♪♪

26:49.033 --> 26:51.955
I'll find out what Baz did to
her and I'll put him away.

26:52.253 --> 26:54.722
Then I'm coming after
the rest of you!

26:57.431 --> 27:00.468
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:04.536 --> 27:05.837
What's up?

27:05.909 --> 27:08.087
- Hey.
- Hey.

27:08.275 --> 27:09.384
What's that?

27:09.432 --> 27:10.619
You like it?

27:10.667 --> 27:12.540
[ Chuckles ] Is it yours?

27:12.990 --> 27:14.900
Yeah, just bought it.

27:15.549 --> 27:17.087
The wheels are kinda big.

27:17.251 --> 27:18.900
Yeah, they're better
for on the sand.

27:19.072 --> 27:21.619
I'm gonna do drive around
for a bit. You wanna come?

27:21.994 --> 27:23.665
You wanna drive around?

27:24.360 --> 27:25.689
Yeah.

27:26.379 --> 27:28.126
Okay. [ Laughs ]

27:38.279 --> 27:39.747
[ Exhales deeply ]

27:42.476 --> 27:45.077
- Hey.
- Hey.

27:45.479 --> 27:47.226
You get my messages?

27:47.479 --> 27:48.523
Yep.

27:48.704 --> 27:49.984
I just want to talk.

27:50.124 --> 27:52.286
I know you don't want me
coming by your house.

27:52.343 --> 27:53.882
No, I know.

27:54.648 --> 27:56.288
- I'm taking my break.
- Man: Yeah, sure.

27:56.336 --> 27:57.838
My son.

28:09.836 --> 28:11.148
No.

28:12.290 --> 28:14.766
I just... wanted you to know
I got a job.

28:14.922 --> 28:16.836
Been sober for three months.

28:17.577 --> 28:19.125
Now you've told me.

28:20.859 --> 28:23.529
Um, look, you're angry.
I get it.

28:23.750 --> 28:25.531
You have every right to be.

28:26.101 --> 28:27.539
You know, Ray, I-I...
[ Lighter clicks ]

28:27.587 --> 28:29.711
to be honest,
I don't remember much of it.

28:29.992 --> 28:31.914
I mean, Smurf loves
to talk about

28:31.992 --> 28:34.289
all the terrible things
you did to me.

28:34.642 --> 28:36.609
I just figured a lot of it
was bullshit,

28:36.815 --> 28:39.492
her just wanting me
to be grateful.

28:40.500 --> 28:42.906
Then I see something
like this.

28:46.683 --> 28:47.784
See that?

28:50.094 --> 28:51.529
[ Sniffles ]

28:52.550 --> 28:55.857
Smurf came to my door that night
with that friend of yours.

28:56.818 --> 28:58.459
Tied me to a chair,

28:59.066 --> 29:01.631
took a pipe to my legs,
to my arms.

29:02.138 --> 29:04.560
Used this like a map.

29:05.959 --> 29:08.716
[ Breathing deeply ]

29:09.663 --> 29:11.623
Smurf didn't save me.

29:12.713 --> 29:14.670
The damage was done.

29:17.559 --> 29:20.787
You're never gonna see me again.
Stop calling me.

29:21.971 --> 29:25.008
[ Footsteps depart ]

29:32.687 --> 29:33.849
Eat.

29:34.241 --> 29:36.076
You gonna feed it to me?

29:39.901 --> 29:42.068
[ Sighs deeply ]

29:42.429 --> 29:44.232
[ Knife clicks ]

29:44.461 --> 29:45.629
[ Grunts ]

29:50.271 --> 29:51.779
What's in it?

29:52.506 --> 29:54.006
Are you kidding me?

29:55.805 --> 29:57.107
[ Sighs ]

30:01.581 --> 30:03.076
Craig: So what's your name?

30:03.583 --> 30:04.802
Alejandro.

30:05.051 --> 30:07.688
Okay, Alejandro, is your dad
a drug dealer? Is that it?

30:07.854 --> 30:10.068
- Cop.
- Cop.

30:10.724 --> 30:12.451
Lots of dirty cops down there.

30:12.592 --> 30:13.990
Connected, too.

30:14.038 --> 30:17.074
Okay, yeah, well, you must think
you're a real badass, huh?

30:17.497 --> 30:19.899
I don't want nothing to do
with that life.

30:20.037 --> 30:24.091
I'm up here, trying to
better myself and shit.

30:25.085 --> 30:26.552
[ Sighs ]

30:29.334 --> 30:31.646
I heard you on the phone, man.

30:32.278 --> 30:34.708
You don't want to be doing this.

30:35.341 --> 30:40.982
Just let me go, and my dad will
get you whatever you want.

30:41.120 --> 30:42.701
[ Pounding on door ]

30:42.756 --> 30:45.058
I swear to God.

30:45.091 --> 30:48.528
Shh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

30:48.562 --> 30:51.090
Uh, yeah, we're... we're closed.
Sorry.

30:51.225 --> 30:53.427
Renn: Craig here?
He told me to come by.

30:58.237 --> 30:59.723
What do you want?

31:00.386 --> 31:03.527
Hey, Deran. Don't be an asshole.
Let me in.

31:05.715 --> 31:07.447
- Renn.
- Renn?

31:07.481 --> 31:08.996
Handle her. Now.

31:09.317 --> 31:12.934
Take care of it.
Go. Just get rid of her.

31:16.090 --> 31:18.105
Go. Now.

31:18.992 --> 31:20.691
[ Office door closes ]

31:21.909 --> 31:23.238
This place is cool.

31:23.422 --> 31:24.754
Thanks.

31:25.446 --> 31:28.590
Um... can I catch you later?

31:28.935 --> 31:30.629
We're doing inventory.

31:31.324 --> 31:33.573
Yeah. I'm just here
to get my money.

31:34.601 --> 31:37.512
I floated you the cash.
You said you'd pay me back.

31:39.262 --> 31:40.926
Yeah. Uh...

31:41.247 --> 31:44.293
Yeah. Wait, wait.
So... what do I owe you?

31:44.539 --> 31:45.824
The plane alone was 11 grand.

31:45.872 --> 31:47.605
- Plane?
- Jesus Christ.

31:47.789 --> 31:50.426
Craig, the private plane
you chartered.

31:50.538 --> 31:53.723
You used the word "baller,"
like, 900 times.

31:54.877 --> 31:56.211
Right.

32:00.552 --> 32:01.778
Don't say shit or I'll...

32:01.826 --> 32:03.160
- [ Grunts ]
- stab you.

32:03.208 --> 32:04.787
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
- Okay?

32:04.935 --> 32:07.427
- Mm.
- [ Under breath ] Goddamn it.

32:08.284 --> 32:10.372
- Craig: I don't have it on me.
- [ Renn scoffs ]

32:10.420 --> 32:11.921
Forgot you were coming.

32:12.112 --> 32:15.115
Fine. Tonight.

32:18.366 --> 32:21.319
Don't show, and I will actually
kill you this time.

32:21.588 --> 32:23.326
- Great.
- Great.

32:23.374 --> 32:26.280
I look forward to it.

32:28.128 --> 32:29.835
[ Sighs ]

32:30.507 --> 32:32.165
Is this fun for you?

32:32.198 --> 32:35.452
[ Locks door ]
No. Man...

32:36.460 --> 32:37.913
[ Inhales deeply ] it's not.

32:38.088 --> 32:39.928
Been doing this shit
our whole lives.

32:40.068 --> 32:41.421
The hell
are you talking about?

32:41.538 --> 32:43.061
You bitch and moan
about Baz and Smurf,

32:43.109 --> 32:45.335
but you can't really do shit
on your own.

32:45.725 --> 32:47.225
Can you?

32:47.975 --> 32:49.986
I mean, the whole yacht thing
was my idea.

32:50.034 --> 32:51.039
They wouldn't have done it

32:51.087 --> 32:52.311
- if I hadn't vouched for you.
- Oh, that's bullshit, man!

32:52.359 --> 32:53.420
I did all the work!

32:53.468 --> 32:55.613
Now you bring this shit
into my bar, which is basically

32:55.661 --> 32:57.488
- the only safe thing in my life.
- What was I supposed to do?

32:57.536 --> 32:59.082
Deal with it, man, for once!

32:59.178 --> 33:01.582
You're the one that told Marco
that we owed him.

33:01.630 --> 33:03.093
Not me! You!

33:03.148 --> 33:04.692
I can't believe I'm gonna
have to deal with this shit

33:04.739 --> 33:05.746
for the rest of my life.

33:05.794 --> 33:08.479
Any time I-I'm remotely good
at something, it can't be mine.

33:08.527 --> 33:09.738
- It has to be ours, always.
- What are we

33:09.786 --> 33:10.964
- talking about here? Surfing?

33:11.012 --> 33:12.880
- No, we're not talking about surfing.
- The only reason that you even

33:12.928 --> 33:14.290
got into that was because of me.

33:14.338 --> 33:15.321
Okay, man.

33:15.376 --> 33:16.986
I drove you to each and every
one of your tournaments,

33:17.034 --> 33:18.532
- wherever they were.
- No, you drove me to the tournaments

33:18.580 --> 33:20.150
so you could tell the girls
that you were my coach,

33:20.198 --> 33:21.876
so they'd sleep with you.
That's why.

33:21.924 --> 33:22.947
- Mm-hmm.
- That's why.

33:22.995 --> 33:25.001
And then... and then
I'd clean up your puke and shit

33:25.049 --> 33:26.978
and drive your drunk ass home
at 14 years old.

33:27.026 --> 33:28.707
You think Smurf was
gonna get up at 4:00

33:28.755 --> 33:30.156
and drive you to San Pedro?

33:30.323 --> 33:31.790
You think Baz was?

33:31.919 --> 33:33.228
Pope?

33:39.864 --> 33:42.066
One of these days,
you're gonna end up dead.

33:42.201 --> 33:43.490
I can't spend
the rest of my life

33:43.538 --> 33:44.756
making sure
that doesn't happen.

33:44.837 --> 33:48.441
So soon as I get enough money
to buy this place,

33:49.077 --> 33:50.935
I'm out.

33:51.831 --> 33:53.165
I'm serious. I'm done.

33:53.246 --> 33:55.081
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

34:00.787 --> 34:02.404
We got an address.

34:02.656 --> 34:05.692
♪♪

34:15.068 --> 34:17.136
Go! [ Shouts indistinctly ]

34:17.170 --> 34:22.842
♪♪

34:22.876 --> 34:25.178
I got him! I got him!

34:26.846 --> 34:28.281
[ Crash ]

34:28.313 --> 34:32.217
[ Grunting ]

34:32.251 --> 34:34.654
Aah! Damn it!

34:34.688 --> 34:36.255
Aah!

34:36.289 --> 34:40.193
[ Grunting ]
[ Thud ]

34:40.226 --> 34:44.063
[ Grunting ]

34:44.097 --> 34:47.076
Enough. Enough! Get off him!

34:47.123 --> 34:49.061
- Enough!
- [ Grunts ]

34:53.715 --> 34:56.751
[ Grunting and gasping ]

34:59.063 --> 35:02.402
They'll make my dad pay
and they'll kill me anyway.

35:02.548 --> 35:05.851
[ Panting ]

35:06.119 --> 35:10.402
Cut me up and send me
back to him in pieces.

35:10.724 --> 35:12.668
It's payback.
Don't you get it?

35:12.959 --> 35:16.136
You take me there,
I'm... I'm dead.

35:16.215 --> 35:20.801
[ Gasping ]

35:20.967 --> 35:24.847
♪♪

35:25.772 --> 35:29.075
[ Engine turns off ]

35:29.210 --> 35:32.935
♪♪

35:35.506 --> 35:36.872
[ Gate clanks ]

36:06.279 --> 36:08.326
[ Velcro rips ]

36:08.374 --> 36:11.177
♪♪

36:16.790 --> 36:19.287
Cath never talked to the cops.

36:20.827 --> 36:22.755
[ Jewelry clatters ]

36:26.069 --> 36:27.356
Andrew...

36:27.404 --> 36:30.287
This detective that stopped Baz,
I followed him,

36:30.441 --> 36:34.946
I confronted him, I got into
his face, and made him tell me.

36:35.248 --> 36:39.257
- You talked to a cop?
- Because I had to know.

36:39.726 --> 36:41.800
He lied. Cops lie.

36:41.848 --> 36:44.577
He wasn't just saying it.

36:44.625 --> 36:46.070
She didn talk.

36:46.118 --> 36:47.853
You told me she talked.

36:48.021 --> 36:49.823
She didn't talk!

36:49.871 --> 36:51.781
She would have,
sooner or later.

36:51.829 --> 36:53.140
[ Breathing deeply ]

36:58.555 --> 36:59.889
[ Thud ]
[ Grunts ]

37:01.419 --> 37:02.687
[ Grunts ]

37:04.534 --> 37:09.273
[ Stifling sobs ]

37:10.072 --> 37:11.867
[ Sniffles ]

37:11.961 --> 37:14.719
[ Crying ]

37:17.216 --> 37:20.945
♪♪

37:26.637 --> 37:30.897
[ Groans ]

37:31.004 --> 37:32.707
Shh, shh.

37:33.430 --> 37:35.622
[ Kissing ]

37:40.268 --> 37:43.271
[ Inhales deeply ]

37:43.468 --> 37:47.273
- [ Whispers indistinctly ]
- Get off me.

37:48.447 --> 37:50.679
[ Sniffles ]

37:51.477 --> 37:54.757
♪♪

38:05.824 --> 38:07.808
[ Sniffs ]

38:07.957 --> 38:09.225
[ Clears throat ]

38:09.258 --> 38:11.795
[ Surf rolling ]

38:12.011 --> 38:16.032
How'd you find this place?

38:16.347 --> 38:19.235
My mom used to meet
her dealer here.

38:19.769 --> 38:22.730
I don't get you.

38:23.261 --> 38:25.058
What do you mean?

38:25.456 --> 38:28.058
If I lived with your mom...
Shooting up all the time,

38:28.284 --> 38:30.580
no food in the house,
no money,

38:30.816 --> 38:33.750
Smurf and your uncles living
a mile away like kings...

38:33.933 --> 38:36.052
I'd be pissed.

38:36.316 --> 38:38.655
You don't even seem angry.

38:42.128 --> 38:44.089
I'm angry all the time.

38:44.393 --> 38:47.631
♪♪

39:02.045 --> 39:03.680
[ Buckle clinking ]

39:03.835 --> 39:07.717
[ Unzips pants ]

39:08.718 --> 39:11.755
♪♪

39:27.650 --> 39:29.088
Janine?
What are you doing here?

39:29.338 --> 39:31.345
Can I come in?

39:43.768 --> 39:46.314
You know I don't do this here
for anyone.

39:46.791 --> 39:48.119
This couldn't wait
till tomorrow?

39:48.220 --> 39:49.275
No.

39:49.323 --> 39:50.549
That yacht's been
all over the news.

39:50.597 --> 39:52.666
Doesn't seem
like your usual style.

39:52.935 --> 39:54.548
It's not.

39:55.865 --> 39:57.852
Well, the cops will
be scouring the U.S. markets,

39:57.900 --> 40:01.478
so I'll have to look for a buyer
in Europe or the Middle East.

40:01.580 --> 40:02.939
It's gonna take
a couple weeks.

40:03.033 --> 40:06.111
I wouldn't be here
if it weren't important.

40:07.103 --> 40:09.619
Smurf, what's going on?

40:11.815 --> 40:14.533
I got a problem,
and I need cash to solve it.

40:14.648 --> 40:16.658
What are we talking about?

40:17.160 --> 40:19.119
Baz.

40:20.135 --> 40:23.797
♪♪

40:47.984 --> 40:49.468
[ Exhales sharply ]

40:51.988 --> 40:54.601
[ Line rings ]

40:56.525 --> 40:58.194
[ Ring ]

40:58.227 --> 40:59.578
Woman: <i>San Diego County
Sheriff's Department</i>.

40:59.626 --> 41:01.433
<i>How can I direct your call?</i>

41:04.173 --> 41:05.741
[ Knife chopping ]

41:05.900 --> 41:07.834
[ Knock on door ]

41:12.186 --> 41:13.358
- Hey.
- Hey.

41:13.406 --> 41:15.718
I thought you weren't coming
till later.

41:16.546 --> 41:17.749
[ Door creaks ]

41:18.753 --> 41:20.851
I need to talk to you.

41:23.132 --> 41:25.382
Yeah. Is something wrong?

41:30.612 --> 41:33.182
[ Knobs click ]

41:33.429 --> 41:38.608
Hey. What's the matter?
What's going on?

41:38.868 --> 41:40.536
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:40.569 --> 41:42.839
[ Whispers ] Andrew.

41:47.249 --> 41:49.491
Do you think forgiveness
is possible?

41:49.813 --> 41:54.405
I do.
I know Jesus' love is absolute.

41:55.601 --> 42:00.223
Is it possible for him to...
[ Inhales shakily ]

42:00.491 --> 42:03.069
[ Voice breaks ]
to love somebody

42:03.843 --> 42:06.819
who's done something horrible?
[ Sobs ]

42:06.954 --> 42:08.823
[ Whispers ] Is it possible?

42:09.087 --> 42:10.218
I hope so.

42:10.595 --> 42:12.087
Could you?

42:12.286 --> 42:15.884
[ Sniffling ]

42:16.472 --> 42:20.844
Andrew, what's wrong?
You can tell me, baby.

42:20.877 --> 42:23.913
♪♪

42:30.019 --> 42:33.823
I hurt someone.

42:33.986 --> 42:36.150
A woman I loved.

42:36.900 --> 42:39.056
I loved her...

42:42.095 --> 42:43.884
but I did it anyway.

42:44.481 --> 42:47.712
Did what? What did you do?

42:50.572 --> 42:53.494
I thought she was going to hurt
my family.

43:01.548 --> 43:03.892
I put a pillow over her face

43:04.759 --> 43:07.611
and I held it there until
she couldn't breathe anymore.

43:08.325 --> 43:11.362
♪♪

43:16.065 --> 43:19.035
[ Speaking inaudibly ]

43:19.068 --> 43:22.923
♪♪

43:22.970 --> 43:26.056
♪♪

44:07.562 --> 44:09.831
[ Oil rig squeaking ]

44:09.879 --> 44:12.413
[ Pounding on trunk ]

44:14.252 --> 44:16.624
You think they're gonna
kill him?

44:17.453 --> 44:18.546
I don't know.

44:18.594 --> 44:20.351
[ Pounding continues ]

44:20.720 --> 44:22.822
You really want out?

44:23.199 --> 44:24.898
[ Pounding on trunk ]

44:25.585 --> 44:28.702
[ Breathes deeply ]

44:29.319 --> 44:30.710
Yeah.

44:31.083 --> 44:33.385
[ Pounding continues ]

44:33.718 --> 44:35.523
Here we go.

44:40.859 --> 44:42.628
[ Engine turns off ] Marco:
You should've seen the fight!

44:42.687 --> 44:45.741
[ Laughs ] Whoo!

44:46.679 --> 44:49.725
Pettis kicked a dude
in the throat. Ahh!

44:50.077 --> 44:52.898
Took him three minutes
to get up.

44:54.297 --> 44:56.199
What the hell's
wrong with you?

44:58.452 --> 45:00.773
Deran: What are they gonna do
with the kid?

45:02.005 --> 45:04.273
Don't worry about it, man.
Where's the keys?

45:08.577 --> 45:10.013
[ Car door opens and closes ]

45:10.163 --> 45:11.577
[ Keys jangle ]

45:12.311 --> 45:13.905
[ Car doors close ]

45:19.484 --> 45:20.898
Man: Ah.

45:20.976 --> 45:22.781
- Alejandro: No, no, no, no, no, no!
-  Let's go.

45:22.829 --> 45:24.379
No, no, no, no!

45:24.427 --> 45:26.429
No! Por favor, por favor no!
No! No!

45:26.462 --> 45:29.432
[ Pleading in Spanish, crying ]

45:29.465 --> 45:33.039
Por favor! Help!
Help, por favor.

45:33.169 --> 45:37.398
[ Sobbing ]

45:37.942 --> 45:39.851
[ Sighs ]

45:40.361 --> 45:43.297
♪♪

45:43.963 --> 45:46.520
There's a little extra in there
for you. [ Car door closes ]

45:46.796 --> 45:48.636
[ Engine starts ]

45:49.375 --> 45:52.047
[ Car departs ]

45:52.255 --> 45:54.157
We're never doing this again,
Marco.

45:54.256 --> 45:56.273
- Okay, bro.
- No, listen to me.

45:56.560 --> 45:58.562
If I ever see you again,
I'm gonna knock you out.

45:58.610 --> 46:00.281
Take the car and strip it down.

46:00.329 --> 46:02.984
- [ Keys jangle ]
- Get a cab. Simple.

46:03.032 --> 46:05.289
[ Vehicle approaching ]

46:05.516 --> 46:06.875
You better go.

46:07.170 --> 46:09.138
[ Chuckles ]

46:12.641 --> 46:13.942
[ Chuckles ]

46:14.477 --> 46:15.734
Hermana, preciosa.

46:16.041 --> 46:17.509
[ Pistol whips ]
Ow! Aah!

46:17.613 --> 46:20.049
[ Speaks Spanish ]

46:20.083 --> 46:21.284
Marco:
Tenía boletos de primera fila!

46:21.340 --> 46:22.515
Cállate!

46:22.607 --> 46:24.576
[ Grunts ]

46:24.820 --> 46:29.523
[ Speaking Spanish ]

46:29.575 --> 46:30.743
Ow. Sí.

46:31.527 --> 46:33.250
- ¿Sí?
- Sí.

46:33.496 --> 46:36.332
[ Speaks Spanish ]

46:36.840 --> 46:38.348
Yeah.

